condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, part A.1 | Description :The Recipient shall carry out the Project through MOH inaccordance with the requirements and details set forth or referred to in the Project Operations Manual. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.2 | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain (a) theCPIB with resources, staff and under terms of reference satisfactory to the Association | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.3 | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain for theduration of the Project implementation, Oblast Hospital Program Oversight Committees at the local government level | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.4(a) | Description :The Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain for theduration of the Project implementation, an Inter-Ministerial Methodological Commission on Health Financing | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.4(b) | Description :The Recipient shall adopt the decision on (i) theimplementation of the hospital financing pilot in three hospitals in Fergana oblast; and (ii) the expansion of the urban model ofprimary health | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.5 | Description :The Recipient shall, through the MOH, submit to the IDA theapproved hospital investment plan for each year and the respective recurrent costs# plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.6 | Description :The Recipient shall, through the MOH, submit to the IDA thestatus of execution of the hospital investments and respective recurrent costs# plan for the preceding year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, Part A.7.Description: The Recipient shall, through the MOH, submit to the IDA reportsfrom the Oblast Hospital Program Oversight Committees on implementation of the hospital improvement program.
